715122f-a.text:
East 116th Street, east from Pleasant Ave. to the Harlem River, showing at the latter the ferry house and slip of the Ferry to Wards Island (seen in the background). Upon the lIsland are portions of two bridge structures: The Triborough and the New York Central Railroad (Hell Gate).
October 6, 1936.
W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.
